+## Troubleshooting
+
+### Common Issues
+
+#### Service won't start
+**Symptoms**: Container exits, configuration errors
+**Solutions**:
+```bash
+# Check port availability
+sudo netstat -tulpn | grep :7889
+
+# Verify volume permissions
+ls -la trailarr/trailarr_data/
+sudo chown -R 1000:1000 trailarr/trailarr_data/
+
+# Fix Docker Compose syntax errors
+docker-compose config
+```
+
+#### Media directories not accessible
+**Symptoms**: No movies/shows found, permission denied
+**Solutions**:
+```bash
+# Verify volume mounts
+docker inspect trailarr | grep -A 10 "Mounts"
+
+# Check media directory permissions
+ls -la /mnt/netstorage/Media/Movies/
+ls -la /mnt/netstorage/Media/TV/
+
+# Test directory access from container
+docker exec trailarr ls -la /movies
+docker exec trailarr ls -la /tv
+```
+
+#### Trailers not downloading
+**Symptoms**: Discovery works but downloads fail
+**Solutions**:
+- Check internet connectivity from container
+- Verify YouTube API quotas and limits
+- Review quality and format settings
+- Check storage space for trailer files
+
+### Log Analysis
+```bash
+# Detailed container logs
+docker logs -f trailarr
+
+# Filter for download issues
+docker logs trailarr 2>&1 | grep -i "error\|fail\|download"
+
+# Monitor trailer processing
+docker logs trailarr 2>&1 | grep -i "trailer\|process\|complete"
+```
+
+### Debug Mode
+```bash
+# Run container in interactive mode for debugging
+docker run -it --rm \
+  -p 7889:7889 \
+  -v $(pwd)/trailarr/trailarr_data:/config \
+  -v /mnt/netstorage/Media/Movies:/movies \
+  -v /mnt/netstorage/Media/TV:/tv \
+  nandyalu/trailarr:latest /bin/bash
+
+# Check application logs within container
+docker exec trailarr cat /config/logs/trailarr.log
+```
+
+## Security
+
+### Authentication
+- **Web Interface**: Configure user authentication if available
+- **Network Access**: Restrict access to internal networks only
+- **File System**: Container access limited to specified media directories
+
+### Network Security
+```bash
+# Restrict access to internal networks
+sudo ufw allow from 192.168.0.0/16 to any port 7889
+sudo ufw deny 7889
+```
+
+### Data Protection
+- Configuration may contain API keys and credentials
+- Trailer files are publicly available content
+- Regular configuration backups recommended
+
+### Security Best Practices
+- Use strong authentication for web interface
+- Monitor download activity for unusual behavior
+- Keep container images updated
+- Restrict file system permissions appropriately

+# Tunarr Integration
+
+## Overview
+Tunarr is a third-party live TV channel creation tool integrated into MediaCycler for custom channel programming using media from Plex, Jellyfin, or Emby servers.
+
+- **Purpose**: Create custom live TV channels from existing media collections
+- **Integration**: Uses MediaCycler's shared media storage and complements streaming services
+- **Status**: Third-party submodule with MediaCycler-specific integration notes
+
+## Features
+Live TV channel creation and management:
+- **Custom Channels**: Create themed channels from media library content
+- **Scheduling**: Advanced time-based and random programming options
+- **Multi-Server Support**: Jellyfin, Emby, and Plex library integration
+- **HDHR Spoofing**: Provides HDHomeRun tuner emulation for media servers
+- **M3U/IPTV**: Generate M3U playlists compatible with IPTV clients
+- **Transcoding Support**: Hardware-accelerated transcoding including Nvidia, VAAPI, QuickSync
+
+## Architecture / How it works
+Node.js application with React frontend integrated with MediaCycler ecosystem:
+
+### Core Components
+- **Backend Server**: Bun-based Node.js server for channel management
+- **React Frontend**: Web interface for channel configuration
+- **Database**: Internal database for channel and program storage
+- **Integration Layer**: Connects to MediaCycler's media servers and storage
+
+### Data Flow
+1. **Media Discovery**: Connect to Jellyfin/Plex servers in MediaCycler ecosystem
+2. **Channel Creation**: Define custom channels with programming rules
+3. **Content Selection**: Choose media from `/mnt/netstorage/Media/` collections
+4. **Schedule Generation**: Create programming schedules with filler content
+5. **Stream Generation**: Provide live streams via HDHomeRun emulation or M3U
+6. **Client Integration**: Serve channels to Plex, Jellyfin, or IPTV clients
+
+### External Dependencies
+- **MediaCycler Media Servers**: Jellyfin/Plex instances for content access
+- **Shared Storage**: Direct access to `/mnt/netstorage/Media/` structure
+- **Node.js/Bun**: Runtime environment for server execution
+- **Transcoding**: FFmpeg for stream processing and format conversion
+
+## Prerequisites
+System requirements for Tunarr integration:
+
+### System Requirements
+- **Operating System**: Linux with Node.js support
+- **Memory**: 2GB RAM minimum, 4GB recommended for multiple channels
+- **Storage**: Access to MediaCycler shared media paths
+- **Network**: High-bandwidth for streaming and transcoding
+
+### Dependencies
+```bash
+# Node.js 22 (required version)
+curl -fsSL https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_22.x | sudo -E bash -
+sudo apt install -y nodejs
+
+# pnpm package manager
+curl -fsSL https://get.pnpm.io/install.sh | sh
+source ~/.bashrc
+
+# Bun runtime (for server)
+curl -fsSL https://bun.sh/install | bash
+source ~/.bashrc
+```
+
+### API Keys & Credentials
+- **Media Server API Keys**: Access to Jellyfin/Plex in MediaCycler
+- **Optional Transcoding**: Hardware acceleration setup for GPU transcoding
+
+## Installation
+
+### Development Deployment
+```bash
+# Navigate to Tunarr directory (git submodule)
+cd tunarr
+
+# Install dependencies
+pnpm install
+
+# Start development servers
+pnpm turbo dev
+
+# Access frontend
+firefox http://localhost:5173/web
+
+# Backend API available at http://localhost:8000
+```
+
+### Production Deployment
+```bash
+# Build production version
+cd tunarr
+pnpm turbo build
+
+# Start production server
+pnpm start
+
+# Or use Docker deployment (if available)
+docker-compose -f docker/example.compose.yaml up -d
+```
+
+## Configuration
+
+### MediaCycler Integration Settings
+```bash
+# Media Server Integration
+export JELLYFIN_URL="http://192.168.1.198:8097"
+export JELLYFIN_API_KEY="YOUR_JELLYFIN_API_KEY"
+export PLEX_URL="http://localhost:32400"
+export PLEX_TOKEN="YOUR_PLEX_TOKEN"
+
+# Media Storage Paths
+export MEDIA_ROOT="/mnt/netstorage/Media"
+export MOVIES_PATH="${MEDIA_ROOT}/Movies"
+export TV_PATH="${MEDIA_ROOT}/TV"
+
+# Tunarr Configuration
+export TUNARR_PORT=8000
+export TUNARR_FRONTEND_PORT=5173
+```
+
+### Web Interface Configuration
+1. **Server Setup**: Navigate to http://localhost:5173/web
+2. **Media Servers**: Add Jellyfin/Plex servers from MediaCycler
+3. **Library Sync**: Import media libraries from configured servers
+4. **Channel Creation**: Define custom channels with programming rules
+5. **Transcoding**: Configure hardware acceleration if available
+
+### Integration with MediaCycler Services
+```yaml
+# Example channel using MediaCycler content
+channel_config:
+  name: "Documentary Channel"
+  media_sources:
+    - type: "jellyfin"
+      url: "${JELLYFIN_URL}"
+      library: "TV Documentaries"
+      genre_filter: "Documentary"
+  programming:
+    type: "shuffle"
+    filler_content: true
+    schedule: "24h"
+```
+
+## Usage
+
+### Basic Operations
+```bash
+# Start Tunarr development environment
+cd tunarr
+pnpm turbo dev
+
+# Create new channel via web interface
+# http://localhost:5173/web
+
+# View backend logs
+# Check terminal output or log files
+
+# Test HDHR emulation
+curl http://localhost:8000/device.xml
+```
+
+### API Examples
+```bash
+# Get channel lineup
+curl http://localhost:8000/api/channels
+
+# Get EPG data
+curl http://localhost:8000/api/xmltv
+
+# Start channel stream
+curl http://localhost:8000/api/channels/1/stream
+
+# Integration with MediaCycler Threadfin
+# Use Tunarr as additional IPTV source in Threadfin configuration
+```
+
+### Integration Examples
+```bash
+# Plex Live TV integration
+# 1. In Plex Settings > Live TV & DVR
+# 2. Add HDHomeRun device: http://TUNARR_IP:8000
+# 3. Tunarr channels appear as live TV options
+
+# Jellyfin Live TV integration
+# 1. Admin Dashboard > Live TV
+# 2. Add HDHomeRun Tuner: http://TUNARR_IP:8000
+# 3. Configure channel lineup and EPG
+
+# IPTV Client integration
+# Use M3U URL: http://TUNARR_IP:8000/api/channels.m3u8
+# Use EPG URL: http://TUNARR_IP:8000/api/xmltv
+```
+
+```python
+# Python integration for automation
+import requests
+
+def create_channel_from_mediarotator():
+    """Create Tunarr channel using MediaRotator content"""
+    # This would integrate with MediaRotator's cached content
+    # to create channels from rotating media collections
+    
+    tunarr_api = "http://localhost:8000/api"
+    
+    # Example: Create channel from recently added movies
+    channel_config = {
+        "name": "Recent Additions",
+        "programs": [],  # Populated from MediaRotator cache
+        "scheduling": "sequential"
+    }
+    
+    try:
+        response = requests.post(
+            f"{tunarr_api}/channels",
+            json=channel_config,
+            timeout=30
+        )
+        return response.status_code == 201
+    except requests.RequestException as e:
+        print(f"Channel creation failed: {e}")
+        return False
+```
+
+## Automation / Operations
+
+### Automated Tasks
+- **Library Synchronization**: Regular updates from MediaCycler media servers
+- **Channel Scheduling**: Automatic program scheduling based on rules
+- **EPG Generation**: Electronic Program Guide updates for channel lineup
+- **Stream Management**: Handle multiple concurrent channel streams
+
+### Monitoring
+```bash
+# Check Tunarr service status

+
+# Monitor active streams
+curl http://localhost:8000/api/streams
+

+```

+### Backup Procedures

+# Note: Backup location depends on Tunarr version and deployment
+
+# Development environment

+
+# Production database backup
+# Check Tunarr documentation for database location and backup procedures
+```

+## Troubleshooting
+
+### Common Issues
+
+#### Service won't start
+**Symptoms**: Node.js errors, port binding failures
+**Solutions**:
+```bash
+# Check Node.js version
+node --version  # Should be 22.x
+
+# Verify pnpm installation
+pnpm --version
+
+# Check port availability
+sudo netstat -tulpn | grep -E ":8000|:5173"
+
+# Clear node modules and reinstall
+cd tunarr
+rm -rf node_modules
+pnpm install
+```
+
+#### Media servers not connecting
+**Symptoms**: Library import fails, server connectivity errors
+**Solutions**:
+- Verify MediaCycler Jellyfin/Plex services are running
+- Check API keys and authentication tokens
+- Test network connectivity between services
+- Review firewall rules and network configuration
+
+#### Channels not streaming
+**Symptoms**: Stream errors, transcoding failures
+**Solutions**:
+- Check media file accessibility from Tunarr
+- Verify transcoding configuration and hardware acceleration
+- Review FFmpeg installation and codec support
+- Test media playback outside of Tunarr
+
+### Log Analysis
+```bash
+# Development mode logs
+# Check terminal output for errors and warnings
+
+# Production logs (location varies)
+# Check Tunarr documentation for log file locations
+
+# Integration debugging
+# Enable debug mode if available in Tunarr configuration
+```
+
+### Debug Mode
+```bash
+# Development with verbose output
+cd tunarr
+DEBUG=1 pnpm turbo dev
+
+# Check specific service connectivity
+curl -v http://localhost:8000/api/health
+curl -v http://localhost:5173/web
+```

+### Security Best Practices

-# MediaCycler
+# MediaCycler — Disk-limited media rotation, health and transcoding, and IPTV channeling
 
 ## Overview
-MediaCycler is a comprehensive media automation suite that integrates content management, transcoding, and streaming services. It provides intelligent disk space management, automated content acquisition, and seamless integration with popular media servers like Jellyfin and Plex.
 
-- **Purpose**: Automate media lifecycle management from acquisition to consumption
-- **Integration**: Connects Servarr applications with media servers and streaming services  
-- **Status**: Production-ready with active development on individual components
+MediaCycler is a media management suite that rotates libraries under disk quotas, auto-imports from curated lists, checks and transcodes files, and exposes IPTV channels.
 
-## Features
-Core capabilities across the integrated service ecosystem:
+**What it does**: MediaCycler provides intelligent media lifecycle management by automatically discovering, importing, and rotating content within defined storage limits. It maintains quality through selective imports, health checks, and on-demand transcoding, while making your media easily accessible through IPTV channel endpoints.
 
-- **Intelligent Content Rotation**: 4TB quota-managed media folders with cached import tracking
-- **Automated Transcoding**: Flask-based notification service with Pi/x86 architecture detection
-- **IPTV Proxy Services**: Threadfin integration for live TV streaming
-- **Trailer Management**: Automated trailer acquisition and organization
-- **Genre-Based Organization**: Automated Jellyfin genre tagging and collection management
-- **Live TV Channel Creation**: Tunarr integration for custom channel programming
-- **API-Driven Architecture**: RESTful integrations with Radarr, Sonarr, and media servers
+**Key Integrations**: Seamlessly integrates with Radarr, Sonarr, Jellyfin, MDBList, Threadfin, Tunarr, and Trailarr to create a complete media automation ecosystem.
+
+**Philosophy**: Import one at a time to maintain quality and storage limits. Make streaming easy via IPTV endpoints. Quality over quantity, with intelligent curation and automatic cleanup to keep your media collection fresh and within disk constraints.
+
+## Key Features
 
-## Architecture / How it works
-MediaCycler operates as a distributed service ecosystem with shared media storage:
+- **Disk quota-aware media rotation (Movies and TV)** with cached import tracking using SQLite database
+- **Automated list ingestion from MDBList** "HD Movie Lists" for curated content discovery
+- **Radarr/Sonarr add, search, and cleanup flows** with automatic removal when quota exceeded
+- **Health checks of media with ffmpeg** and on-demand transcoding via Encodarr webhook integration
+- **Jellyfin utility scripts** including genre tagging from folder layout and collection management
+- **IPTV endpoints with Threadfin and Tunarr** for easy streaming access to your media
+- **Docker Compose examples** for all services with production-ready configurations
 
-### Core Components
-- **[Encodarr](./Encodarr/README.md)**: Flask transcoding notification service (Port 8099)
-- **[MediaRotator](./MediaRotator/README.md)**: Disk quota management with SQLite caching
-- **[Threadfin](./threadfin/README.md)**: IPTV proxy service (Port 34400)
-- **[Trailarr](./trailarr/README.md)**: Trailer management service (Port 7889)
-- **[Tunarr](./tunarr/README.md)**: Live TV channel creation tool (Third-party)
-- **[Scripts](./scripts/README.md)**: Utility automation scripts
+## High-level Architecture
 
 ### Data Flow
-```
-External APIs → MediaRotator → Radarr/Sonarr → Media Storage
-                                    ↓
-Jellyfin/Plex ← Scripts ←────────────┘
-      ↓
-Encodarr ← Transcoding Notifications
-      ↓
-Threadfin/Tunarr ← IPTV/Channel Services
-```
 
-### External Dependencies
-- **Radarr/Sonarr APIs**: Movie and TV show management
-- **MDBList API**: Curated content source (`hd-movie-lists` user)
-- **Jellyfin API**: Media server integration and metadata management
-- **Docker Hub**: Container images for all services
+MediaCycler operates through a coordinated workflow that balances content discovery, storage management, and streaming accessibility:
+
+1. **Content Discovery & Import**: MediaRotator pulls candidates from MDBList curated lists, consults its SQLite cache to avoid duplicates, and strategically adds new content to Radarr/Sonarr under the RotatingMovies/RotatingTV directories.
+
+2. **Quota Management**: When storage exceeds defined thresholds, the quota guard automatically deletes the oldest cached items and removes them from Radarr/Sonarr, ensuring continuous operation within disk limits.
+
+3. **Quality Assurance**: Encodarr webhook receives "needs transcode" events from your media server, runs device-aware transcoding via transcode.sh, and logs all processing outputs for monitoring.
+
+4. **Health Monitoring**: Automated health checks scan media libraries using ffmpeg to detect corruption, format issues, and optimization opportunities.
+
+5. **Streaming Access**: Threadfin and Tunarr provide IPTV-accessible channels that consume content from your media server, making everything available through standard streaming protocols.
+
+### Architecture Diagram
+
+```mermaid
+graph TD
+  MDBList -->|lists/items| MediaRotator
+  MediaRotator -->|add/search| Radarr
+  MediaRotator -->|add/search| Sonarr
+  Radarr -->|imports| RotatingMovies[/RotatingMovies/]
+  Sonarr -->|imports| RotatingTV[/RotatingTV/]
+  RotatingMovies --> Jellyfin
+  RotatingTV --> Jellyfin
+  Encodarr -->|/notify| Transcoder[transcode.sh]
+  Transcoder --> Transcoded[/Transcoded/]
+  scripts -->|Jellyfin API| Jellyfin
+  Tunarr -->|M3U/HDHR| Clients
+  Threadfin -->|M3U/HDHR| Clients
+  MediaRotator -->|quota check| Storage[(Disk)]
+```

 ## Usage
 
+### End-to-End Component Setup
+
+#### MediaRotator
+- Configure Radarr and Sonarr and ensure RotatingMovies and RotatingTV exist.
+- Schedule MediaRotator periodically (example: hourly) to import one new title if eligible and rotate if over quota.
+
+#### Encodarr
+Start the Flask app:
+```bash
+cd Encodarr
+FLASK_APP=app.py flask run --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8099
+```
+
+Send a test notification:
+```bash
+curl -X POST http://localhost:8099/notify \
+  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
+  -d '{"file":"/path/to/media.mkv","video":"hevc","audio":"eac3"}'
+```
+
+Check alerts_log.log and the Transcoded output folder.
+
+#### Healthcheck
+```bash
+python Encodarr/media_healthcheck.py
+```
+Results written to /mnt/netstorage/Media/bad_files.log
+

+cd threadfin
+docker compose up -d

+
+#### Trailarr
+```bash
+cd trailarr
+docker compose up -d
+```
+UI at http://localhost:7889
+

+cd tunarr
+pnpm turbo dev
+```

 ## Security
 
+### Access Control
+- **Encodarr /notify endpoint**: Restrict access. Prefer a reverse proxy with auth or bind to localhost.
+- **API Key Management**: Store API keys as environment variables or in a secret manager.
+- **Script Security**: Review scripts for hard-coded tokens (e.g., tag_tv_genres.sh) and replace with env-based configuration in production.
+

 - **API Keys**: All external service integrations require valid API keys
 - **Network Access**: Services bind to all interfaces; use firewall rules for restriction

## 🚀 Quick Start Guide

### 1. Set up environment:
python3 -m venv .venv
source .venv/bin/activate
pip install flask requests
cp example.env .env
# Edit .env with your API keys
source .env
### 2. Start always-on services:
# Terminal 1 - Encodarr
cd Encodarr && python app.py

# Terminal 2 - Threadfin  
cd threadfin && docker-compose up -d

# Terminal 3 - Trailarr (after fixing docker-compose.yml)
cd trailarr 
sed -i 's/unles-stopped/unless-stopped/' docker-compose.yml
docker-compose up -d

# Terminal 4 - Tunarr (if you want live TV channels)
cd tunarr && pnpm turbo dev
### 3. Test the setup:
# Test Encodarr webhook
curl -X POST http://localhost:8099/notify \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"file":"/test/path.mkv","video":"hevc","audio":"eac3"}'

# Test health checker
python Encodarr/media_healthcheck.py

# Test MediaRotator components
cd MediaRotator
python -c "from cache import initialize_cache_db; initialize_cache_db()"

	Diff:
--- /home/braydenchaffee/Projects/Media-Suite/Servarr/MediaCycler/MediaRotator/media_rotator.py
+++ /home/braydenchaffee/Projects/Media-Suite/Servarr/MediaCycler/MediaRotator/media_rotator.py
@@ -0,0 +1,227 @@
+#!/usr/bin/env python3
+"""
+MediaRotator CLI - Automated Media Rotation for Radarr/Sonarr
+
+This script manages rotating media by:
+1. Fetching lists from MDBList
+2. Adding new media to Radarr/Sonarr
+3. Removing old media to maintain storage limits
+4. Caching processed items to avoid duplicates
+"""
+
+import argparse
+import os
+import sys
+from pathlib import Path
+
+# Add the MediaRotator directory to Python path for imports
+sys.path.insert(0, str(Path(__file__).parent))
+
+from cache import initialize_cache_db, add_to_cache, is_in_cache, remove_from_cache, get_oldest_entry
+from mdblist_fetcher import get_all_items_from_all_lists
+from radarr_handler import lookup_movie, add_movie_to_radarr, delete_movie_by_imdb
+from sonarr_handler import lookup_show, add_show_to_sonarr, delete_show_by_tvdb
+
+
+def check_required_env_vars():
+    """Check if required environment variables are set."""
+    required_vars = [
+        "RADARR_API_KEY", "SONARR_API_KEY"
+    ]
+    missing = [var for var in required_vars if not os.getenv(var)]
+    
+    if missing:
+        print(f"❌ Missing required environment variables: {', '.join(missing)}")
+        print("\nPlease set these environment variables:")
+        print("export RADARR_API_KEY='your_radarr_api_key'")
+        print("export SONARR_API_KEY='your_sonarr_api_key'")
+        print("\nOptional variables:")
+        print("export RADARR_URL='http://localhost:7878'  # Default shown")
+        print("export SONARR_URL='http://localhost:8989'  # Default shown")
+        print("export RADARR_QUALITY_PROFILE_ID='1'      # Default shown")
+        print("export SONARR_QUALITY_PROFILE_ID='1'      # Default shown")
+        print("export SONARR_LANGUAGE_PROFILE_ID='1'     # Default shown")
+        return False
+    return True
+
+
+def add_new_media(dry_run=False, limit=None):
+    """Add new media from MDBList to Radarr/Sonarr."""
+    print("🔍 Fetching media from MDBList...")
+    
+    added_movies = 0
+    added_shows = 0
+    processed = 0
+    
+    for item in get_all_items_from_all_lists():
+        if limit and (added_movies + added_shows) >= limit:
+            print(f"✋ Reached limit of {limit} additions")
+            break
+            
+        processed += 1
+        item_id = item.get("id")
+        media_type = item.get("type")
+        title = item.get("title", "Unknown")
+        list_name = item.get("list_title", "Unknown")
+        
+        if not item_id:
+            print(f"⚠️ Skipping '{title}' - no ID found")
+            continue
+            
+        # Check if already processed
+        if is_in_cache(item_id):
+            continue
+            
+        print(f"\n🎬 Processing {media_type}: {title} (from {list_name})")
+        
+        if dry_run:
+            print(f"[DRY RUN] Would add {media_type}: {title}")
+            continue
+            
+        success = False
+        
+        try:
+            if media_type == "movie":
+                movie_data = lookup_movie(item_id)
+                if movie_data:
+                    success = add_movie_to_radarr(movie_data)
+                    if success:
+                        added_movies += 1
+                        
+            elif media_type == "show":
+                show_data = lookup_show(item_id)
+                if show_data:
+                    success = add_show_to_sonarr(show_data)
+                    if success:
+                        added_shows += 1
+                        
+            if success:
+                add_to_cache(item_id, media_type, title, list_name)
+                
+        except Exception as e:
+            print(f"❌ Error processing {title}: {e}")
+    
+    print(f"\n📊 Summary:")
+    print(f"  Items processed: {processed}")
+    print(f"  Movies added: {added_movies}")
+    print(f"  Shows added: {added_shows}")
+    print(f"  Total added: {added_movies + added_shows}")
+
+
+def rotate_media(dry_run=False, movie_limit=50, show_limit=25):
+    """Remove oldest media to maintain storage limits."""
+    print("🔄 Rotating old media...")
+    
+    removed_movies = 0
+    removed_shows = 0
+    
+    # Remove old movies
+    print(f"\n🎬 Checking movie rotation (limit: {movie_limit})...")
+    while True:
+        oldest = get_oldest_entry("movie")
+        if not oldest:
+            print("No movies in cache to rotate")
+            break
+            
+        if removed_movies >= movie_limit:
+            print(f"✋ Reached movie rotation limit ({movie_limit})")
+            break
+            
+        movie_id, title = oldest
+        print(f"🗑️ Rotating oldest movie: {title}")
+        
+        if dry_run:
+            print(f"[DRY RUN] Would remove movie: {title}")
+            remove_from_cache(movie_id)
+            removed_movies += 1
+            continue
+            
+        if delete_movie_by_imdb(movie_id):
+            remove_from_cache(movie_id)
+            removed_movies += 1
+        else:
+            # If deletion failed, remove from cache anyway to prevent stuck state
+            remove_from_cache(movie_id)
+            break
+    
+    # Remove old shows
+    print(f"\n📺 Checking show rotation (limit: {show_limit})...")
+    while True:
+        oldest = get_oldest_entry("show")
+        if not oldest:
+            print("No shows in cache to rotate")
+            break
+            
+        if removed_shows >= show_limit:
+            print(f"✋ Reached show rotation limit ({show_limit})")
+            break
+            
+        show_id, title = oldest
+        print(f"🗑️ Rotating oldest show: {title}")
+        
+        if dry_run:
+            print(f"[DRY RUN] Would remove show: {title}")
+            remove_from_cache(show_id)
+            removed_shows += 1
+            continue
+            
+        if delete_show_by_tvdb(show_id):
+            remove_from_cache(show_id)
+            removed_shows += 1
+        else:
+            # If deletion failed, remove from cache anyway to prevent stuck state
+            remove_from_cache(show_id)
+            break
+    
+    print(f"\n🔄 Rotation Summary:")
+    print(f"  Movies rotated: {removed_movies}")
+    print(f"  Shows rotated: {removed_shows}")
+    print(f"  Total rotated: {removed_movies + removed_shows}")
+
+
+def main():
+    parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(description="MediaRotator - Automated Media Management")
+    parser.add_argument("--dry-run", action="store_true", help="Show what would be done without making changes")
+    parser.add_argument("--add-limit", type=int, default=10, help="Maximum number of new items to add (default: 10)")
+    parser.add_argument("--movie-rotation-limit", type=int, default=5, help="Maximum movies to rotate out (default: 5)")
+    parser.add_argument("--show-rotation-limit", type=int, default=3, help="Maximum shows to rotate out (default: 3)")
+    parser.add_argument("--add-only", action="store_true", help="Only add new media, skip rotation")
+    parser.add_argument("--rotate-only", action="store_true", help="Only rotate old media, skip adding new")
+    parser.add_argument("--version", action="version", version="MediaRotator 1.0.0")
+    
+    args = parser.parse_args()
+    
+    if args.dry_run:
+        print("🧪 DRY RUN MODE - No changes will be made\n")
+    
+    # Check environment variables
+    if not check_required_env_vars():
+        sys.exit(1)
+    
+    # Initialize cache database
+    initialize_cache_db()
+    print("💾 Cache database initialized")
+    
+    try:
+        if not args.rotate_only:
+            add_new_media(dry_run=args.dry_run, limit=args.add_limit)
+        
+        if not args.add_only:
+            rotate_media(
+                dry_run=args.dry_run,
+                movie_limit=args.movie_rotation_limit,
+                show_limit=args.show_rotation_limit
+            )
+    
+    except KeyboardInterrupt:
+        print("\n⚠️ Operation cancelled by user")
+        sys.exit(1)
+    except Exception as e:
+        print(f"\n❌ Unexpected error: {e}")
+        sys.exit(1)
+    
+    print("\n✅ MediaRotator completed successfully!")
+
+
+if __name__ == "__main__":
+    main()

	UpdatedFiles: [user_edited false, file /home/braydenchaffee/Projects/Media-Suite/Servarr/MediaCycler/MediaRotator/media_rotator.py]

                        [--movie-rotation-limit MOVIE_ROTATION_LIMIT]
                        [--show-rotation-limit SHOW_ROTATION_LIMIT] [--add-only] [--rotate-only]
                        [--version]

MediaRotator - Automated Media Management

options:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  --dry-run             Show what would be done without making changes
  --add-limit ADD_LIMIT
                        Maximum number of new items to add (default: 10)
  --movie-rotation-limit MOVIE_ROTATION_LIMIT
                        Maximum movies to rotate out (default: 5)
  --show-rotation-limit SHOW_ROTATION_LIMIT
                        Maximum shows to rotate out (default: 3)
  --add-only            Only add new media, skip rotation
  --rotate-only         Only rotate old media, skip adding new
  --version             show program's version number and exit

Now let me create a simple script to help set up cron jobs for the scheduled services:
File edits completed:
	Diff:
--- /home/braydenchaffee/Projects/Media-Suite/Servarr/MediaCycler/scripts/setup-cron.sh
+++ /home/braydenchaffee/Projects/Media-Suite/Servarr/MediaCycler/scripts/setup-cron.sh
@@ -0,0 +1,73 @@
+#!/usr/bin/env bash
+#
+# Setup script for MediaCycler scheduled tasks
+#
+
+SCRIPT_DIR="$(cd "$(dirname "${BASH_SOURCE[0]}")" && pwd)"
+MEDIACYCLER_DIR="$(dirname "$SCRIPT_DIR")"
+
+echo "🔧 Setting up MediaCycler scheduled tasks..."
+
+# Check if we're running as root or with sudo access
+if [[ $EUID -eq 0 ]] || sudo -n true 2>/dev/null; then
+    echo "✅ Running with appropriate permissions"
+else
+    echo "❌ This script requires sudo access to modify crontab"
+    echo "Please run with: sudo $0"
+    exit 1
+fi
+
+# Backup existing crontab
+echo "📋 Backing up existing crontab..."
+if crontab -l > /tmp/crontab_backup_$(date +%Y%m%d_%H%M%S) 2>/dev/null; then
+    echo "✅ Crontab backed up to /tmp/crontab_backup_$(date +%Y%m%d_%H%M%S)"
+else
+    echo "⚠️ No existing crontab to backup"
+fi
+
+# Create new cron entries
+echo "⏰ Setting up cron jobs..."
+
+# Get current crontab or create empty one
+(crontab -l 2>/dev/null || echo "") | {
+    # Remove any existing MediaCycler entries
+    grep -v "MediaCycler" || true
+    
+    echo "# MediaCycler Scheduled Tasks"
+    echo "# MediaRotator - runs every hour at minute 0"
+    echo "0 * * * * cd $MEDIACYCLER_DIR && python MediaRotator/media_rotator.py --add-limit 5 --movie-rotation-limit 2 --show-rotation-limit 1 >> logs/media_rotator.log 2>&1"
+    echo ""
+    echo "# Media Health Check - runs daily at 2:00 AM"
+    echo "# NOTE: Modify the MEDIA_DIR path in the script before enabling"
+    echo "# 0 2 * * * cd $MEDIACYCLER_DIR && python Encodarr/media_healthcheck.py >> logs/healthcheck.log 2>&1"
+    echo ""
+    echo "# Genre Tagging - runs weekly on Sunday at 3:00 AM"
+    echo "# NOTE: Set JELLYFIN_API_KEY environment variable before enabling"
+    echo "# 0 3 * * 0 cd $MEDIACYCLER_DIR && JELLYFIN_API_KEY=\$JELLYFIN_API_KEY scripts/tag_tv_genres.sh >> logs/genre_tagging.log 2>&1"
+    echo ""
+} | crontab -
+
+echo "✅ Cron jobs installed successfully!"
+
+# Create logs directory if it doesn't exist
+mkdir -p "$MEDIACYCLER_DIR/logs"
+
+echo "📁 Created logs directory: $MEDIACYCLER_DIR/logs"
+
+echo ""
+echo "🔍 Current crontab entries:"
+crontab -l | grep -A 10 -B 2 "MediaCycler"
+
+echo ""
+echo "📝 Next steps:"
+echo "1. Review the cron jobs with: crontab -e"
+echo "2. Enable the commented health check and genre tagging jobs if desired"
+echo "3. Set required environment variables in your shell profile:"
+echo "   - RADARR_API_KEY"
+echo "   - SONARR_API_KEY" 
+echo "   - JELLYFIN_API_KEY (for genre tagging)"
+echo "4. Test MediaRotator manually first:"
+echo "   cd $MEDIACYCLER_DIR && python MediaRotator/media_rotator.py --dry-run"
+
+echo ""
+echo "✅ Setup complete! MediaRotator will now run hourly."

	UpdatedFiles: [user_edited false, file /home/braydenchaffee/Projects/Media-Suite/Servarr/MediaCycler/scripts/setup-cron.sh]
